## `pozi_base.qgs` — WMS layer structure (live)

The Flutter app talks to this project. Layer hierarchy (depth 0 = WMS root, depth 1 = wrapper, depth 2 = study/base groups, depth 3 = leaves):

```
[GROUP] (root)
  [GROUP] WCMA                                     ← single wrapper around everything
    [GROUP] Concongella 2015 Flood Depths          ← study group (name ends with " Flood Depths")
      [LEAF]  Concongella 0.5% (1 in 200yr)
      [LEAF]  Concongella 1% (1 in 100yr)          ← default-on (substring "1% (1 in 100")
      [LEAF]  Concongella 2% (1 in 50yr)
      ... (6 recurrence levels)
    [GROUP] Dunmunkle 2017 Flood Depths
      [LEAF]  Rupanyup Post Mitigation 1% (1 in 100yr)   ← lives under Dunmunkle, not its own group
      [LEAF]  Dunmunkle 0.5% (1 in 200yr)
      ...
    [GROUP] Halls Gap 2017 Flood Depths            ← 6 recurrence levels each
    [GROUP] Horsham Wartook 2019 Flood Depths
    [GROUP] Lower Wimmera 2016 Flood Depths
    [GROUP] Mt William 2014 Flood Depths
    [GROUP] Natimuk 2013 Flood Depths              ← contains Natimuk Township + Natimuk Catchment leaves
    [GROUP] Stawell 2024 Flood Depths              ← 16 leaves: 8x Stawell Flood Depths + 8x Stawell Golf
    [GROUP] Upper Wimmera 2014 Flood Depths
    [GROUP] Warracknabeal Brim 2015 Flood Depths
    [GROUP] Wimmera River Yarriambiack Creek 2010 Flood Depths
    [GROUP] Base Layers
      [LEAF]  Flood Investigation Study Areas
      [LEAF]  Rivers and Streams
      [LEAF]  Wetlands
      [LEAF]  River Gauges
      [LEAF]  Historic River Gauges
      [LEAF]  Parcels
      [LEAF]  Wimmera CMA Boundary                 ← excluded from app's "Base Layers" panel (used for boundary fit only, locally)
```

Conventions the app relies on:
- A study group is **any group whose `<Name>` ends with `' Flood Depths'`**, located at any depth (currently depth 2).
- `Base Layers` is a uniquely-named group, located at any depth.
- The app extracts both recursively (so the `WCMA` wrapper is transparent to it).
- Default-on leaves are those whose name contains `'1% (1 in 100'`.

